<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<vector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:width="108dp"
    android:height="108dp"
    android:viewportWidth="108"
    android:viewportHeight="108">
    <!--
      Only the middle 72dp of this 108dp canvas survives the launcher's mask.
      Sized off Gmail, the closest Google icon in spirit (a wide shape in the same
      circle): its ink spans 70% of the mask's diameter, so the folder is 50dp wide.
      Height follows from proportion rather than the mask - at the old 56x34 the
      folder was flat enough (1.65) that its corners crowded the rim while the space
      above and below it sat empty. 50x36 (1.39, near Material's own folder glyph)
      keeps the same visual weight with the corners pulled in to a 29.2dp radius.

      One path, evenOdd: the X is punched out of the folder as a hole rather than
      painted over it in the background colour. On the launcher icon
      the hole exposes the same @color/ic_launcher_background, so it looks identical -
      but this drawable is also the monochrome layer, and a themed icon tints every
      opaque pixel one colour. Painted on top, the X would flatten into the folder and
      vanish; as a hole it stays transparent and survives the tint.
    -->
    <path
        android:fillColor="#FFFFFFFF"
        android:fillType="evenOdd"
        android:pathData="M33,36 L45,36 L49,42 L75,42 A4,4 0 0 1 79,46 L79,68 A4,4 0 0 1 75,72 L33,72 A4,4 0 0 1 29,68 L29,40 A4,4 0 0 1 33,36 Z M47,50 L51,50 L54,54.5 L57,50 L61,50 L56.4,57 L61,64 L57,64 L54,59.5 L51,64 L47,64 L51.6,57 Z" />
</vector>
